{"TopicId":82777,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"The Kerbal Elevator: Abusing KSP physics for fun and profit!","CreatedByName":"GusTurbo","CreatedById":57552,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T01:22:46Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"GusTurbo","CreatedById":57552,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T01:22:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EEver wanted to move Kerbals around instantaneously within the confines of the stock game? Look no more. All you need is a command chair and a little creativity.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022 contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003E\u003Ciframe width=\u0022480\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/CfyvekRDi5o?feature=oembed\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EHow it works:\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe key to getting this to work is to place a command chair inside of another part. When you have done this successfully, leaving the command chair will cause the kerbal to pop out on top of whatever object is above it, moving head-first. This extends to any part on top of the original part blocking the point of exit. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dbmorpher","CreatedById":77927,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T01:57:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EDoes this work in micro-gravity?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GusTurbo","CreatedById":57552,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T02:04:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI haven\u0027t tested that yet. I could probably use \u0022Hack Gravity\u0022 in the debug menu to replicate the effect.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E[update]\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ve tested it with hack gravity and it works.\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-08-25T02:51:34Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2014 02:51  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by GusTurbo\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Razz","CreatedById":119692,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T02:56:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ea teleporter - watch out for flys\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"leax256","CreatedById":57364,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T03:49:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI\u0027ve seen this bug before. discovered it durring a livestream.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"JDCollie","CreatedById":103176,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T06:05:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EClean documentation and presentation, I like it \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Overfloater","CreatedById":94031,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T07:03:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/threads/66465-Work-in-Progress-WIP-Design-Thread?p=1097356\u0026amp;viewfull=1#post1097356\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022text-decoration:underline;\u0022\u003EThis guy\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/a\u003E could really have used it...\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E...on his RSS Venus lander\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://dl.dropboxusercontent.com/u/22015656/VenusChuteManouver.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022VenusChuteManouver.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222014-08-25T07:12:43Z\u0022 title=\u002208/25/2014 07:12  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00229 yr\u0022\u003EAugust 25, 2014\u003C/time\u003E by Overfloater\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Masetto","CreatedById":115203,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T07:07:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EKerbal Youtubers always have good music choice. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Majorjim!","CreatedById":61954,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T10:17:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENice one Gus. Ive always wondered if the \u0027popping up\u0027 kerbal phenomenon could be exploited. Could be a way of simulating crew transfer?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EDoes it work with two long ships docked together?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Kasuha","CreatedById":81781,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T10:43:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENice abuse of physics \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E I have noticed the behavior before but never realized it could be used this way.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"EpicRootHairCell","CreatedById":102408,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T10:59:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EAll hail the kraken!\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"GusTurbo","CreatedById":57552,"CreatedDateTime":"2014-08-25T14:00:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Majorjim\u0022 data-cite=\u0022Majorjim\u0022\u003E\u003Cdiv\u003ENice one Gus. Ive always wondered if the \u0027popping up\u0027 kerbal phenomenon could be exploited. Could be a way of simulating crew transfer?\u003Cp\u003EDoes it work with two long ships docked together?\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/div\u003E\u003C/blockquote\u003E\u003Cp\u003EFurther testing is required. \u003Cimg src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 alt=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EI had actually thought about using this for an Eve lander like the one Overfloater posted.\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}